"No, leave me alone," said Princess Mary. 
Her voice sounded so serious and so sad that the chirping of the birds was silenced at once. 
They looked at the beautiful, large, thought- ful eyes full of tears and of thoughts, gazing shiningly and imploringly at them, and under- stood that it was useless and even cruel to in- sist.
